<subSubSection id="C33E6531CC57FFE0FF68C8BDFECFFB48" box="[151,267,1230,1257]" pageId="7" pageNumber="286" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B9B36BACC57FFE0FF68C8BDFECFFB48" blockId="7.[151,633,1194,1257]" box="[151,267,1230,1257]" pageId="7" pageNumber="286">
(
<figureCitation id="131F2A3FCC57FFE0FF60C8BDFEC7FB48" box="[159,259,1230,1257]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 5" captionStart-1="FIGURE 6" captionStartId-0="8.[151,250,1914,1938]" captionStartId-1="9.[151,250,1972,1996]" captionTargetBox-0="[157,1429,645,1877]" captionTargetBox-1="[189,1397,633,1949]" captionTargetId-0="figure-204@8.[151,1436,633,1891]" captionTargetId-1="figure-233@9.[189,1397,633,1949]" captionTargetPageId-0="8" captionTargetPageId-1="9" captionText-0="FIGURE 5. Calepitrimerus huayanlingense sp. nov. AD, prodorsal shield; CG, female coxigenital area; em, empodium; IG, female internal genitalia; L1, leg І; L2, leg II; DM, dorsal view of telosoma; VM, ventral view of telosoma. Scale bar: 15 μm for AD, CG, DM, IG, L1, L2, VM; 3 μm for em." captionText-1="FIGURE 6. Calepitrimerus huayanlingense sp. nov. A, dorsal view; B, prodorsal shield; C, female coxigenital area; D, female internal genitalia; E, tarsus and empodium. Scale bar: 20 μm for A; 10 μm for B, C; 5 μm for D, E." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524516" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524518" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6524516/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6524518/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="286">Figs 5–6</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33E6531CC57FFEFFF68C964FE49FE70" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="287" pageId="7" pageNumber="286" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B9B36BACC57FFE0FF68C964FBBCFA3C" blockId="7.[151,1437,1302,2013]" pageId="7" pageNumber="286">
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC57FFE0FF68C964FEBFFA91" bold="true" box="[151,379,1302,1328]" pageId="7" pageNumber="286">Diagnosis (female).</emphasis>
Body fusiform; prodorsal shield with a broad frontal lobe, median, admedian, and submedian lines present, formed by discontinuous granules, and many granules; legs with 4-rayed simple tarsal empodium, and knobbed tarsal solenidion; opisthosoma dorsally with elliptical microtubercles, while ventrally with elliptical to linear microtubercles; female genital coverflap with many granules at base and 11 striae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9B36BACC57FFEFFF38C9D5FCE7FE0F" blockId="7.[151,1437,1302,2013]" lastBlockId="8.[151,1437,151,609]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="287" pageId="7" pageNumber="286">
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC57FFE0FF38C9D5FEDAFA60" bold="true" box="[199,286,1447,1473]" pageId="7" pageNumber="286">Female</emphasis>
(n = 11, dorsal view): Body fusiform (
<figureCitation id="131F2A3FCC57FFE0FD2CC9D5FC8EFA63" box="[723,842,1447,1474]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1972,1996]" captionTargetBox="[189,1397,633,1949]" captionTargetId="figure-233@9.[189,1397,633,1949]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 6. Calepitrimerus huayanlingense sp. nov. A, dorsal view; B, prodorsal shield; C, female coxigenital area; D, female internal genitalia; E, tarsus and empodium. Scale bar: 20 μm for A; 10 μm for B, C; 5 μm for D, E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524518" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6524518/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="286">Figure 6A</figureCitation>
), 218 (198–218) long, 70 (67–70) wide; light yellow in colour. Gnathosoma 17 (16–19) long, projecting obliquely downwards, cheliceral stylets 19 (17–19), pedipalp coxal seta (
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC57FFE0FEEAC99DFEEBF9A9" box="[277,303,1519,1544]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="286">ep</emphasis>
) 3 (2–3), dorsal pedipalp genual setae (
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC57FFE0FD18C99DFD31F9A8" box="[743,757,1519,1545]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="286">d</emphasis>
) 6 (5–6), palp tarsal ventral setae (
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC57FFE0FB88C99DFB47F9A9" box="[1143,1155,1519,1544]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="286">v</emphasis>
) absent. Prodorsal shield 53 (51–58), including the frontal lobe, 70 (65–70) wide, frontal lobe broad; median, admedian, and submedian lines present, formed by discontinuous granules; many granules present on whole prodorsal shield (
<figureCitation id="131F2A3FCC57FFE0FB38CA45FAF6F9F0" box="[1223,1330,1590,1617]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1914,1938]" captionTargetBox="[157,1429,645,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-204@8.[151,1436,633,1891]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Calepitrimerus huayanlingense sp. nov. AD, prodorsal shield; CG, female coxigenital area; em, empodium; IG, female internal genitalia; L1, leg І; L2, leg II; DM, dorsal view of telosoma; VM, ventral view of telosoma. Scale bar: 15 μm for AD, CG, DM, IG, L1, L2, VM; 3 μm for em." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524516" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6524516/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="286">Figures 5</figureCitation>
AD, 6B). Scapular tubercles ahead of rear shield margin, setae 
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC57FFE0FD13CA29FCC7F9D5" box="[748,771,1627,1652]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="286">sc</emphasis>
7 (6–7), 24 (24–25) apart, projecting centered. Coxigenital region (
<figureCitation id="131F2A3FCC57FFE0FF0FCA0DFE99F938" box="[240,349,1662,1689]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1914,1938]" captionTargetBox="[157,1429,645,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-204@8.[151,1436,633,1891]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Calepitrimerus huayanlingense sp. nov. AD, prodorsal shield; CG, female coxigenital area; em, empodium; IG, female internal genitalia; L1, leg І; L2, leg II; DM, dorsal view of telosoma; VM, ventral view of telosoma. Scale bar: 15 μm for AD, CG, DM, IG, L1, L2, VM; 3 μm for em." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524516" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6524516/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="286">Figures 5</figureCitation>
CG, 6C) with 10 (10–12) semiannuli between coxae and genitalia, with microtubercles; coxal plates with granules, anterolateral setae on coxisternum І (
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC57FFE0FCD9CAD1FC86F91C" box="[806,834,1699,1725]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="286">1b</emphasis>
) 9 (9–10), 14 (13–14) apart; proximal setae on coxisternum І (
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC57FFE0FEF8CAB5FEE0F940" box="[263,292,1735,1761]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="286">1a</emphasis>
) 15 (15–17), 9* apart; proximal setae on coxisternum ІІ (
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC57FFE0FC54CAB5FC03F940" box="[939,967,1735,1761]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="286">2a</emphasis>
) 34 (32–36), 29 (28–29) apart. Prosternal apodeme 6 (6–8). Leg І (
<figureCitation id="131F2A3FCC57FFE0FE56CA99FDDAF8A4" box="[425,542,1770,1797]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1914,1938]" captionTargetBox="[157,1429,645,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-204@8.[151,1436,633,1891]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Calepitrimerus huayanlingense sp. nov. AD, prodorsal shield; CG, female coxigenital area; em, empodium; IG, female internal genitalia; L1, leg І; L2, leg II; DM, dorsal view of telosoma; VM, ventral view of telosoma. Scale bar: 15 μm for AD, CG, DM, IG, L1, L2, VM; 3 μm for em." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524516" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6524516/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="286">Figure 5L</figureCitation>
<figureCitation id="131F2A3FCC57FFE0FDE1CA98FDECF8A4" box="[542,552,1770,1797]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1897,1921]" captionTargetBox="[166,1425,569,1859]" captionTargetId="figure-230@2.[151,1436,561,1874]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Calepitrimerus liuanense sp. nov. AD, prodorsal shield; CG, female coxigenital area; em, empodium; GM, male external genitalia; IG, female internal genitalia; L1, leg І; L2, leg II; DM, dorsal view of telosoma; VM, ventral view of telo- soma. Scale bar: 15 μm for AD, CG, DM, GM, IG, L1, L2, VM; 5 μm for em." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524508" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6524508/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="286">1</figureCitation>
) 33 (33–35), femur 10 (10–11), basiventral femoral setae (
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC57FFE0FB4ACA99FB0BF8A4" box="[1205,1231,1771,1797]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="286">bv</emphasis>
) 11 (10–11); genu 5*, antaxial genual setae (
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC57FFE0FE3BCB7DFE1CF888" box="[452,472,1807,1833]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="286">l''</emphasis>
) 21 (21–23); tibia 8 (8–9), paraxial tibial setae (
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC57FFE0FBF6CB7DFBD3F888" box="[1033,1047,1807,1833]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="286">l'</emphasis>
) 7 (6–7), located at center; tarsus 6*, paraxial fastigial tarsal setae 
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC57FFE0FDF7CB41FDDAF8EC" box="[520,542,1843,1869]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="286">ft’</emphasis>
21 (19–21), antaxial fastigial tarsal setae 
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC57FFE0FC0CCB41FBD7F8EC" box="[1011,1043,1843,1869]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="286">ft’’</emphasis>
22 (21–22), setae 
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC57FFE0FB1CCB41FB33F8EC" box="[1251,1271,1843,1869]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="286">u'</emphasis>
6 (5–6); tarsal empodium (
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC57FFE0FEDFCB25FE85F8D1" box="[288,321,1879,1904]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="286">em</emphasis>
) 5 (5–6), simple, 4-rayed, tarsal solenidion (
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC57FFE0FCC3CB25FC94F8D1" box="[828,848,1879,1904]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="286">ω</emphasis>
) 6 (5–6), knobbed. Leg ІІ (
<figureCitation id="131F2A3FCC57FFE0FB78CB25FB3EF8D0" box="[1159,1274,1878,1905]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1914,1938]" captionTargetBox="[157,1429,645,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-204@8.[151,1436,633,1891]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Calepitrimerus huayanlingense sp. nov. AD, prodorsal shield; CG, female coxigenital area; em, empodium; IG, female internal genitalia; L1, leg І; L2, leg II; DM, dorsal view of telosoma; VM, ventral view of telosoma. Scale bar: 15 μm for AD, CG, DM, IG, L1, L2, VM; 3 μm for em." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524516" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6524516/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="286">Figure 5L</figureCitation>
<figureCitation id="131F2A3FCC57FFE0FB05CB24FACCF8D0" box="[1274,1288,1878,1905]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1938,1962]" captionTargetBox="[162,1425,181,1914]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[162,1425,181,1914]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Calepitrimerus liuanense sp. nov. A, dorsal view of male; B, prodorsal shield; C, female coxigenital area; D, female internal genitalia; E, tarsus and empodium; F, male coxigenital area. Scale bar: 20 μm for A, D; 10 μm for B, C, F; 5 μm for D, E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524510" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6524510/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="286">2</figureCitation>
) 28 (28–30), femur 9 (9–10), basiventral femoral setae (
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC57FFE0FD7CCB09FD59F834" box="[643,669,1915,1941]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="286">bv</emphasis>
) 11 (10–11); genu 5 (4–5), antaxial genual setae (
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC57FFE0FB1FCB09FB30F834" box="[1248,1268,1915,1941]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="286">l''</emphasis>
) 9 (7–9); tibia 6*; tarsus 6*, paraxial fastigial tarsal setae 
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC57FFE0FD86CBEDFD4BF818" box="[633,655,1951,1977]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="286">ft’</emphasis>
5 (5–6), antaxial fastigial tarsal setae 
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC57FFE0FBC6CBEDFB9CF818" box="[1081,1112,1951,1977]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="286">ft’’</emphasis>
22 (20–22), setae 
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC57FFE0FAD7CBEDFAF8F818" box="[1320,1340,1951,1977]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="286">u'</emphasis>
5 (4–5); tarsal empodium (
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC57FFE0FE99CBB1FE43F87D" box="[358,391,1987,2012]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="286">em</emphasis>
) 6 (5–6), simple, 4-rayed, tarsal solenidion (
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC57FFE0FC79CBB1FC5EF87D" box="[902,922,1987,2012]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="286">ω</emphasis>
) 6*, knobbed. Opisthosoma dorsally with 44 (43–44) semiannuli, with elliptical microtubercles, with three ridges, middorsal ridge ended on 27–28 annuli, in a broad furrow (
<figureCitation id="131F2A3FCC58FFEFFEADCCC9FE08FF77" box="[338,460,187,214]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1972,1996]" captionTargetBox="[189,1397,633,1949]" captionTargetId="figure-233@9.[189,1397,633,1949]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 6. Calepitrimerus huayanlingense sp. nov. A, dorsal view; B, prodorsal shield; C, female coxigenital area; D, female internal genitalia; E, tarsus and empodium. Scale bar: 20 μm for A; 10 μm for B, C; 5 μm for D, E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524518" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6524518/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="287">Figure 6A</figureCitation>
); ventrally with 71 (70–73) semiannuli, with elliptical to linear microtubercles. Setae 
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC58FFEFFF68CCADFF76FF58" box="[151,178,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="287">c2</emphasis>
27 (24–27), on ventral semiannulus 11 (11–12), 56 (51–56) apart; setae 
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC58FFEFFC0ECCADFC3BFF58" box="[1009,1023,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="287">d</emphasis>
45 (45–50), on ventral semiannulus 26 (25–26), 35 (33–35) apart; setae 
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC58FFEFFDD1CD71FDFEFEBD" box="[558,570,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="287">e</emphasis>
23 (22–25), on ventral semiannulus 48 (46–48), 14 (14–15) apart; setae 
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC58FFEFFA8ECD71FABDFEBC" box="[1393,1401,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="287">f</emphasis>
31 (25–31), 27 (25–27) apart, on 6th ventral semiannulus from rear; setae 
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC58FFEFFC33CD55FC23FEE0" box="[972,999,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="287">h1</emphasis>
3 (2–3), setae 
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC58FFEFFB69CD55FB77FEE0" box="[1174,1203,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="287">h2</emphasis>
78 (65–78). Female genitalia 19 (17–19), 25 (23–25) wide, coverflap with many granules at base and 11 striae, setae 
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC58FFEFFB2CCD39FB2BFEC4" box="[1235,1263,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="287">3a</emphasis>
30 (25–30), 18 (17–18) apart. Internal genitalia: spermathecae ovoid, oriented posterolaterad; spermathecal tubes relatively short; transverse genital apodeme trapezoidal (
<figureCitation id="131F2A3FCC58FFEFFDA5CDE1FD00FE0C" box="[602,708,402,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1914,1938]" captionTargetBox="[157,1429,645,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-204@8.[151,1436,633,1891]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Calepitrimerus huayanlingense sp. nov. AD, prodorsal shield; CG, female coxigenital area; em, empodium; IG, female internal genitalia; L1, leg І; L2, leg II; DM, dorsal view of telosoma; VM, ventral view of telosoma. Scale bar: 15 μm for AD, CG, DM, IG, L1, L2, VM; 3 μm for em." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524516" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6524516/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="287">Figures 5</figureCitation>
IG, 6D).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9B36BACC58FFEFFF38CDC5FE49FE70" blockId="8.[151,1437,151,609]" box="[199,397,439,465]" pageId="8" pageNumber="287">
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC58FFEFFF38CDC5FEC0FE70" bold="true" box="[199,260,439,465]" pageId="8" pageNumber="287">Male</emphasis>
: Not found.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
