<subSubSection id="C33E6531CC59FFEEFF38CCC9FCF5FF58" pageId="9" pageNumber="288" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B9B36BACC59FFEEFF38CCC9FCF5FF58" blockId="9.[151,1437,150,609]" pageId="9" pageNumber="288">
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC59FFEEFF38CCC9FE8AFF74" bold="true" box="[199,334,187,213]" pageId="9" pageNumber="288">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific designation 
<taxonomicName id="4C244D39CC59FFEEFD94CCC9FCDFFF74" authorityName="Xue &amp; Liu" authorityYear="2022" box="[619,795,187,213]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Calepitrimerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="huayanlingense">
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC59FFEEFD94CCC9FCDFFF74" box="[619,795,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="288">huayanlingense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is derived from the name of location, where the new species was collected, adding a postfix - 
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC59FFEEFDCBCCADFDA2FF59" box="[564,614,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="288">ense</emphasis>
; neuter in gender.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33E6531CC59FFEEFF38CD70FD44FDC0" pageId="9" pageNumber="288" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B9B36BACC59FFEEFF38CD70FD44FDC0" blockId="9.[151,1437,150,609]" pageId="9" pageNumber="288">
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC59FFEEFF38CD70FE0BFEBD" bold="true" box="[199,463,258,284]" pageId="9" pageNumber="288">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
We compared the new species with three 
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC59FFEEFC53CD71FB92FEBC" box="[940,1110,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="288">Calepitrimersu</emphasis>
mites because they all infest 
<taxonomicName id="4C244D39CC59FFEEFF68CD55FF39FEE0" box="[151,253,295,321]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Moraceae" genus="Ficus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="9" pageNumber="288" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC59FFEEFF68CD55FF11FEE1" box="[151,213,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="288">Ficus</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C244D39CC59FFEEFEF3CD55FE45FEE0" box="[268,385,295,321]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Moraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="9" pageNumber="288" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Moraceae</taxonomicName>
). The new species can be differentiated from 
<taxonomicName id="4C244D39CC59FFEEFC81CD55FBF9FEE0" authority="Wei, 2004" authorityName="Wei" authorityYear="2004" box="[894,1085,295,321]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Calepitrimerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fici">
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC59FFEEFC81CD55FC07FEE0" box="[894,963,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="288">C. fici</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB54B4BCC59FFEEFC35CD55FBF9FEE0" author="Wei, S. - G. &amp; Li, Z. - L. &amp; Chen, J. - W." box="[970,1085,295,321]" pageId="9" pageNumber="288" pagination="75 - 80" refId="ref8969" refString="Wei, S. - G., Li, Z. - L. &amp; Chen, J. - W. (2004) Four new species of Phyllocoptinae (Acari: Eriophyidae) from China. Entomotaxonomia, 26 (1), 75 - 80." type="journal article" year="2004">Wei, 2004</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(infest 
<taxonomicName id="4C244D39CC59FFEEFB6CCD55FACBFEE0" box="[1171,1295,295,321]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Moraceae" genus="Ficus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="9" pageNumber="288" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirta">
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC59FFEEFB6CCD55FACBFEE0" box="[1171,1295,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="288">Ficus hirta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) by median, admedian, and submedian lines formed by discontinuous granules (median, admedian, and submedian lines present in 
<taxonomicName id="4C244D39CC59FFEEFF4ACD1DFF3EFE28" authorityName="Wei" authorityYear="2004" box="[181,250,367,393]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Calepitrimerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fici">
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC59FFEEFF4ACD1DFF3EFE28" box="[181,250,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="288">C. fici</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), setae 
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC59FFEEFEAECD1DFEA9FE28" box="[337,365,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="288">h1</emphasis>
present (setae 
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC59FFEEFDE8CD1DFDF6FE28" box="[535,562,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="288">h1</emphasis>
absent in 
<taxonomicName id="4C244D39CC59FFEEFD58CD1DFD28FE28" authorityName="Wei" authorityYear="2004" box="[679,748,367,393]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Calepitrimerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fici">
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC59FFEEFD58CD1DFD28FE28" box="[679,748,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="288">C. fici</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and empodium 4-rayed (empodium 5-rayed in 
<taxonomicName id="4C244D39CC59FFEEFAEBCD1DFA9DFE28" authorityName="Wei" authorityYear="2004" box="[1300,1369,367,393]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Calepitrimerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fici">
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC59FFEEFAEBCD1DFA9DFE28" box="[1300,1369,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="288">C. fici</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The new species can also be differentiated from 
<taxonomicName id="4C244D39CC59FFEEFD82CDE1FBEEFE0C" authority="Mohanasundaram, 1982" authorityName="Mohanasundaram" authorityYear="1982" box="[637,1066,403,429]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Calepitrimerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="asperrimae">
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC59FFEEFD82CDE1FCD9FE0D" box="[637,797,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="288">C. asperrimae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB54B4BCC59FFEEFCDCCDE1FBEEFE0C" author="Mohanasundaram, M." box="[803,1066,403,429]" pageId="9" pageNumber="288" pagination="249 - 263" refId="ref8459" refString="Mohanasundaram, M. (1982) Indian eriophyid studies III. Acarologia, 23 (3), 249 - 263." type="journal article" year="1982">Mohanasundaram,1982</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(infest 
<taxonomicName id="4C244D39CC59FFEEFB81CDE1FAFAFE0D" box="[1150,1342,403,428]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Moraceae" genus="Ficus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="9" pageNumber="288" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="exasperata">
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC59FFEEFB81CDE1FAFAFE0D" box="[1150,1342,403,428]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="288">Ficus exasperata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and 
<taxonomicName id="4C244D39CC59FFEEFA7CCDE1FDF8FE70" authority="Mondal &amp; Chakrabarti, 1983" authorityName="Mondal &amp; Chakrabarti" authorityYear="1983" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Calepitrimerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hispidis">
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC59FFEEFA7CCDE1FF2AFE70" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="288">C. hispidis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB54B4BCC59FFEEFF09CDC5FDF8FE70" author="Mondal, S. &amp; Chakrabarti, S." box="[246,572,439,465]" pageId="9" pageNumber="288" pagination="417 - 424" refId="ref8482" refString="Mondal, S. &amp; Chakrabarti, S. 1983. Studies on the eriophyid mites (Acarina: Eriophyoidea) of India IX. New species of Calepitrimerus with a key to Indian species. Acarologia, 24 (4), 417 - 424." type="journal article" year="1983">Mondal &amp; Chakrabarti, 1983</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(infest 
<taxonomicName id="4C244D39CC59FFEEFD6CCDC5FCEEFE70" box="[659,810,439,465]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Moraceae" genus="Ficus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="9" pageNumber="288" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hispida">
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC59FFEEFD6CCDC5FCEEFE70" box="[659,810,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="288">Ficus hispida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) by median, admedian, and submedian lines formed by discontinuous granules (prodorsal shield with lines granules in 
<taxonomicName id="4C244D39CC59FFEEFC9BCDA9FBC1FE55" authorityName="Mohanasundaram" authorityYear="1982" box="[868,1029,475,501]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Calepitrimerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="asperrimae">
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC59FFEEFC9BCDA9FBC1FE55" box="[868,1029,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="288">C. asperrimae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; median, admedian, and submedian lines not formed by granules in 
<taxonomicName id="4C244D39CC59FFEEFDFDCD8DFDBFFDB8" authorityName="Mondal &amp; Chakrabarti" authorityYear="1983" box="[514,635,511,537]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Calepitrimerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hispidis">
